OOP:Object Oriented Programming

Features of OOP:
1)Object:Any entity which has own state and behaviour
ex:pen,paper etc..[Any Living things]

2)Class:Collection of objects[Having a data members]
ex:Human Body

3)Abstraction:Hiding internal details and 
showing funcitonalities
ex:Login Page

4)Encapsualtion:Wrapping or Binding up of data
ex:Zip File[Capsule]

5)Inheritance:When One object acquire all the properites and 
behaviour of parent class

6)Polymorphism:Many ways to perform anything
ex:Ways

Package
Without Package-Default Package

Syntax for object creation:

Classname objname =new classname();

UserInput=>

printf->system.out.println()
scanf->Scanner


int
Integer

Constructor=>when method having a same name as a classname
parameter[argument]
types of constructor
1)Default
2)Parameterized
3)Copy


Refrence Keyword->this

Static=>Fixed
1)Variable
2)Method
3)Block

